        <para>When one prepares to catalogue a publication inside Tamboti, one has first to decide which type of publication it is. The question one must first
            answer is whether the publication is:</para>
        <ul>
            <li>a monograph</li>
            <li>an edited volume</li>
            <li>a contribution to an edited volume</li>
            <li>a periodcal</li>
            <li>an article in a periodical</li>
            <li>a monograph series</li>
        </ul>
        <para>The next choice one is confronted with is whether the publication is written in a script that is not Latin, for instance in Arabic or Chinese. If
            this is the case, one would then normally want to transliterate (transcribe, romanise) most of the bibliograhical information and perhaps translate
            the title. This obviouly requires more input fields, but it makes the bibliographical entry much more useful to others, who may not know the
            language in question. Each of the six publication types therefore come in two variants, one "plain" and one with transliteration.</para>
